-- Russia's Rosneft 2022 bond at record low on sanctions on CEO
-- By Sujata Rao
-- Mon Apr 28, 2014 09:29AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, April 28 (Reuters) - Dollar bonds issued by Russia's state-controlled oil firm Rosneft <ROSN.MM> fell to a record low on Monday after the United States announced sanctions against company CEO Igor Sechin.

The 2022 bond <XS086198118=TE> was half a cent lower to  83.5 cents on the dollar. Sechin, an ally of Russian President Vladimir Putin, is the most powerful energy executive to be targeted by sanctions so far. [ID:nL6N0NK3UI]. The bond has fallen 10 cents since the start of the year.